sql:
SELECT total_flight_hours
FROM aircraft
ORDER BY total_flight_hours DESC;

external_knowledge:
- Average fuel efficiency refers to the total fuel efficiency of an aircraft model during the cruise phase, divided by the number of flights for that model.; 
- Completed flights refer to flights that have finished and have a recorded status of 'Completed'.; 
- The cruise phase is a stage of flight where the aircraft flies at a steady altitude and speed.
